The paper proposes a reformulation of Variational Auto-Encoders (VAEs) in a deep network setting, which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the optimization of the variational lower bound objective, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to image data, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of closed form solutions, which is a topic in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT).
